# 🏛️ The Law

**Frédéric Bastiat • 1850**

> *“The law is the organization of the natural right of lawful defense.”*

An **[Open Knowledge Format (OKF)](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/blob/main/okf/SPEC.md)** knowledge bundle that turns Bastiat’s classic essay into a richly-linked, machine-readable concept graph.

---

## ✨ What’s Here

This repository is a **git-friendly, human-readable + agent-friendly** representation of Bastiat’s argument:

- **True purpose of law** — the collective organization of defense for natural rights (life, liberty, property).
- **Legal plunder** — when law is perverted by greed or “false philanthropy” into an instrument that takes from some to give to others.
- **Consequences** of perverted law and the case for returning government to its strictly negative, protective sphere.

The content is organized as a navigable directory tree of Markdown files with YAML frontmatter, extensive bidirectional cross-links, and computed graph analytics.

---

## 🧠 Core Argument at a Glance

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph True Law
        TL[Law as Organization<br/>of Collective Defense]
        NR[Natural Rights<br/>Life • Liberty • Property]
    end

    subgraph Perversion
        FP[False Philanthropy]
        GR[Greed & Political Struggle]
        LP[Legal Plunder]
    end

    subgraph Consequences
        DM[Demoralization of Citizens]
        CC[Class Conflict]
        RS[Rent-Seeking]
        EI[Economic Impoverishment]
        ER[Effacing of Justice]
    end

    TL --> NR
    NR -->|When perverted| LP
    FP --> LP
    GR --> LP

    LP --> DM
    LP --> CC
    LP --> RS
    LP --> EI
    LP --> ER

    style TL fill:#d1fae5,stroke:#10b981
    style LP fill:#fee2e2,stroke:#ef4444
    style Consequences fill:#fef3c7,stroke:#f59e0b
```

**Key insight**: Law is either a shield for everyone’s rights… or a sword for some people’s desires.

